text: Robinson is an extinct town in Okanogan County, in the U.S. state of Washington. The GNIS classifies it as a populated place. A post office called Robinson was established in 1900, and remained in operation until 1902. The community had the name of James Robinson, a pioneer hunter. ==References== Category:Ghost towns in Washington (state) Category:Geography of Okanogan County, Washington
title: Robinson, Washington
